00002 Print current actual axis angles from SDH.
00003 
00004 - Example usage:
00005   - Print actual angles of an SDH connected via Ethernet:
00006     The SDH has IP-Address 192.168.1.42 and is attached to TCP port 23.
00007     (Requires at least SDH-firmware v0.0.3.1)
00008     > demo-GetAxisActualAngle.py --tcp=192.168.1.42:23 
00009     
00010   - Print actual angles of an SDH connected to port 2 = COM3 once:
00011     > demo-GetAxisActualAngle.py -p 2
00012     
00013   - Print actual angles of an SDH connected to port 2 = COM3 every 500ms:
00014     > demo-GetAxisActualAngle.py -p 2 -t 0.5
00015      
00016   - Get the version info of both the joint controllers and the tactile 
00017     sensor firmware from an SDH connected via Ethernet. 
00018     The SDH and the tactile sensors have a common IP-Address,
00019     here 192.168.1.42. The joint controller is attached to the
00020     TCP port 23 and the tactile sensors to TCP port 13000.
00021     (Requires at least SDH-firmware v0.0.3.2)
00022     > demo-GetAxisActualAngle.py --tcp=192.168.1.42:23 --dsa_tcp=:13000 -v
00023 
00024   - Get the version info of both the joint controllers and the tactile 
00025     sensor firmware from an SDH connected to:
00026     - port 2 = COM3 (joint controllers) and 
00027     - port 3 = COM4 (tactile sensor controller) 
00028     > demo-GetAxisActualAngle.py --port=2 --dsaport=3 -v
